{:proof/problem-id "apm-t99J04", :proof/classification :partial, :proof/output "\n\n---\n\nTARGET SANITY CHECK — mentions-problem-objects? ✅ (the artifacts explicitly reference the manifolds X and Y, the smooth functions \\(f^i\\), the map \\(f\\), and their differentials) · avoids-assuming-conclusion? ✅ (the Lean targets assert the coordinate-chart and surjectivity results without prebaking the conclusions) · meaningful-without-prose? ✅ (each statement is a standalone theorem about local diffeomorphisms). Notes: part (a) relies directly on the inverse function theorem, while part (b) adds the compact/connected argument; Mathlib has the ingredients but not the packaged corollary.\n\n```\nPROOF-PLAN.EDN\n{:goal \"Show that linearly independent differentials give a local coordinate chart and use that to prove a compact-source local diffeomorphism onto a connected target is surjective.\"\n :terms [{:name \"inverse function theorem\"\n          :meaning \"If the Jacobian of F = (f¹,…,fⁿ) at x is invertible, F restricts to a diffeomorphism from a neighborhood of x onto an open set of ℝⁿ.\"\n          :needed-because \"This produces the local coordinate system demanded in part (a).\"}\n         {:name \"local diffeomorphism\"\n          :meaning \"A map with everywhere-invertible derivative is locally a diffeomorphism, hence an open map with discrete fibers.\"\n          :needed-because \"Part (b) reduces to understanding the image of such a map.\"}\n         {:name \"open-and-closed image argument\"\n          :meaning \"The image of a compact space under a continuous map is compact (so closed) and, when the map is open, also open.\"\n          :needed-because \"In a connected target, an open-and-closed subset must be all of Y, giving surjectivity.\"}]\n :strategy [{:id :s1\n             :formal-dependency \"Manifold.inverse_function_theorem\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Apply the inverse function theorem to F = (f¹,…,fⁿ) to exhibit coordinates.\"\n             :why-this-now \"This resolves part (a) outright and supplies the local diffeomorphism input for part (b).\"\n             :lean-target \"In Lean: from `LinearIndependent (dfᵢ x)` deduce that `(fun y ↦ (f¹ y,…,fⁿ y))` is a chart map at x.\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Mathlib already proves the inverse function theorem for smooth maps between finite-dimensional manifolds.\"}\n            {:id :s2\n             :formal-dependency \"Manifold.compact_local_diffeomorphism_surjective\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Use that f is open and proper (compact source) to show its image is nonempty, open, and closed, hence all of Y.\"\n             :why-this-now \"This solves part (b), leveraging the conclusion of part (a).\"\n             :lean-target \"A Lean theorem stating that a smooth map between connected manifolds with compact source and invertible differentials is surjective.\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Mathlib does not currently bundle this exact corollary, but it has the ingredients (inverse function theorem plus topological facts).\"}]\n :stage-status {:stage1 :done :stage2 :done :stage3 :in-progress :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n```\nFORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n{:main-claim {:informal-claim \"If f : X → Y is a smooth map between compact and connected manifolds with invertible differentials everywhere, then f is surjective.\"\n              :formal-name \"compact_local_diffeomorphism_surjective\"\n              :formal-target \"theorem compact_local_diffeomorphism_surjective (f : X ⟶ Y) (h₁ : CompactSpace X) (h₂ : ConnectedSpace Y) (h₃ : ∀ x, IsInvertible (df f x)) : Function.Surjective f\"\n              :sanity-check {:mentions-problem-objects? true\n                             :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true\n                             :meaningful-without-prose? true\n                             :notes \"Captures part (b) precisely: compact source, connected target, everywhere-invertible differential implies surjectivity.\"}}\n :alignments [{:formal-name \"compact_local_diffeomorphism_surjective\"\n               :formal-statement \"Surjectivity of a compact-source local diffeomorphism onto a connected manifold.\"\n               :informal-clause \"Stage 1 part (b).\"\n               :role :main-theorem}\n              {:formal-name \"inverse_function_coordinates\"\n               :formal-statement \"If df¹ₓ,…,dfⁿₓ are linearly independent then F = (f¹,…,fⁿ) is a coordinate chart near x.\"\n               :informal-clause \"Stage 1 part (a).\"\n               :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\nFilled the frame for t99J04:\n\n- `execute.md` now contains full Stage 1–4 content (inverse-function-theorem proof of part (a), surjectivity proof for part (b), dependency graph, Lean status, and next steps).\n- `proof-plan.edn` records the goal, terms (inverse function theorem, local diffeomorphism, open/closed image), strategies `s1`/`s2`, and stage-status map.\n- `formal-alignment.edn` links the informal claim about compact-source local diffeomorphisms being surjective to the intended Lean theorem, with the helper lemma for the coordinate chart.\n- `changelog.edn` now logs workspace initialization, target-check, Stage 1–2 write-up, and the Stage 3 blocker (Mathlib lacks the compact-local-diffeomorphism surjectivity lemma).", :proof/extraction {:phases {}, :dependency-graph nil, :arse-questions nil, :classification :partial, :phase-count 0, :dep-graph-count 0, :arse-count 0}, :proof/frame-workspace {:frame/lean-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/T99J04/Apm_v2_t99J04_1775013570926", :frame/id "apm-v2-t99J04-1775013570926", :workspace/owner-repo "futon6", :workspace/generated-at "2026-04-01T03:19:30.949188Z", :frame/shared-extension-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Local", :frame/module-root "ApmCanaries.Frames.T99J04.Apm_v2_t99J04_1775013570926", :proof/problem-id "t99J04", :workspace/schema "proof-frame-workspace.v1", :frame/workspace-root "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t99J04/apm-v2